# Project Memory Rules

This project uses RememberIt for cross-project knowledge sharing.

## When to search memory

At the START of each conversation, before writing any code, call `recall_memory` with a query describing what the user wants to do. This checks if relevant solutions, patterns, or decisions already exist from past sessions.

Always search memory when:
- Working on API integrations or external service calls
- Making architecture or technology decisions
- Debugging non-trivial errors
- Setting up configuration or deployment
- The user references past work or other projects

## When to save memory

After completing a task, call `remember_it` to save any knowledge that would be useful in future sessions or other projects:
- Architecture decisions and WHY they were made
- Non-obvious debugging solutions (root cause + fix)
- API endpoint behaviors or gotchas
- Project conventions that aren't in the docs
- Integration patterns between services

Do NOT save routine code changes or well-known information.
